-- import: fpm

-- ft.page: Input Example
toc: $config.examples-toc


-- ft.markdown: 

In this example we see an input field. If you type anything it's value is stored
in a ftd variable, and the value of variable is used in the message below the
input.

-- optional string query:

-- object obj:
function: console-print
value: $query

-- ftd.column:
padding: 20
spacing: 20

-- ftd.input:
placeholder: Type Something Here...
width: 400
border-width: 2
$on-input$: $query=$VALUE
$on-change$: message-host $obj

-- ftd.text:
color if $ftd.dark-mode: $fpm.color.main.text

You have typed: {value}

--- ftd.text value: $query
color: $fpm.color.main.text
role: $fpm.type.label-big